You can change the face from Watch Face Details after purchasing the face.

To enable live watch faces, please ensure that the '**Always On Display**' feature on your watch is turned off.

You can turn it off by following these steps 
1. Go to  **Settings** app from your Apple Watch
2. Open **Display and Brightness**
3. Scroll down and Click “**Always On**”
4. Turn it off

**Congratulations!!!**

Live Watch Faces should be working fine from now. If you are facing any other issues, don't forget to contact us at contact@watchfaceswizard.com

items.description:
To enable live watch faces, please ensure that the '**Always On Display**' feature on your watch is turned off.

You can turn it off by following these steps 
1. Go to  **Settings** app from your Apple Watch
2. Open **Display and Brightness**
3. Scroll down and Click “**Always On**”
4. Turn it off

**Congratulations!!!**

Live Watch Faces should be working fine from now. If you are facing any other issues, don't forget to contact us at contact@watchfaceswizard.com

Can't add Watch Faces to your watch? Don't worry; we've got you covered.

If '**Face sharing not available**' appears when attempting to '**Add Face to Watch**,' simply follow these steps to add the faces to your watch:

1. Tap the **Share Icon** on the right side of '**Add Face to Watch**.'

2. Choose the **Watch App** from the share screen; this should allow you to add the face to you watch.



For **Older Apple Watch Series**, the faces will be available in your **Photo Library** app (for Photo and Live Watch Faces).

1. Locate the faces you've added on your '**Photo Library**'.

2. Click the **Share Icon** on the bottom left of your **Photo Library**.

3. Select '**Create Watch Faces**.'

If you encounter any other problems, feel free to contact us at contact@watchfaceswizard.com
